The paper focuses on understanding user behavior and intent in image search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and human-computer interaction (HC). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to classify user intent, which falls under natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) subfields such as computational linguistics (CL). Additionally, the paper analyzes search logs and user interactions with image search engines, which involves multimedia (MM) and computer vision (CV) techniques.
